The paper discusses modelling information cascades over online social networks, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC) and complex systems (cs.CYBER). The paper also uses a simple model of global cascades, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or mathematical aspects of computer science (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of 'superspreaders' and the influence of highly connected nodes, which could fall under the category of social influence (cs.SI).
